posts.description:
"If Allie and Dizzy had a motto it would be: Where's the squeaker?" ~ Cassandra

At six, Allie is a couple of years older than Dizzy. Both thrive on training and adore doing tricks. Allie has a headstart on her fur-brother (although he's catching up in leaps and bounds) and has even given public demonstrations of her pawsome ability to spin, walk through arms, put balls in buckets & more.

How do you do two amazing things in one day?

You photograph an adorable dog like Mabel in the stunning Sugar Pines (a bucket list destination for Mabel's humans and me!). The towering pines proved inspiring ~ it was like walking in a natural cathedral. Even the ground felt special as fallen pine needles formed a springy mattress underfoot. What better place to capture the happy pounding of paws than here?
